transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viacra, this is Olivia speaking, who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 2: My name is Mark Morrison.

Speaker 1: Hi Mark, how are you?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Good, I'm so glad to hear that. How can I help you today, Mark?

Speaker 2: I want to return those pills I got because they didn't work for me.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I can definitely help you with that.

Speaker 1: Okay, so the email we have on file is mark, M-A-R-K dot Morrison at ApacheCorp.com, is that right?

Speaker 2: Yes, that's right.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so I have two options. One is I can either email you the instructions for how to return it, and of course you can do that, and you have 90 days, or if you were interested, I could send you a free sample of 10 pills of their newest, highest quality stuff, which it looks like you haven't tried, as a replacement.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And then, so obviously I wouldn't charge you for it, right? But it is a superior prescription, and we do think it would work for you.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And either way, whether it did or didn't, you would have until June to let us know.

Speaker 2: Okay, well, I can try that.

Speaker 1: Okay, cool.

Speaker 2: All right, so I'm going to send it out to you.

Speaker 1: It's going to be 10 pills at 100 milligrams.

Speaker 2: Can I ship it to 2203 Quail Place Drive, Missouri City, Texas 77489?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, great.

Speaker 1: So, yeah, you should receive these in the next three to five business days, probably by next Wednesday or Thursday.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And as long as you take them on an empty stomach, that's really important for how well they can work for you, and you avoid alcohol when you take them. They should definitely work for you, and I certainly hope they do.

Speaker 2: And just let us know either way by June, because the scripts will be placed on hold for you until then.

Speaker 1: Okay, sounds good.

Speaker 2: All right, thank you so much, Mark.

Speaker 1: All right, bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Yeah, have a great day.

Speaker 1: Bye.
